  "title": "MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Roles & Responsibilities</p><p></p><p>* Lead end-to-end project implementation using appropriate project management methodologies, tools, and best practices to ensure successful delivery.</p><p>* Work closely with stakeholders to gather, analyze, and document project requirements.</p><p>* Ensure assigned projects meet defined requirements, timelines, and quality standards, and are aligned with the company’s strategic objectives.</p><p>* Establish and maintain effective project governance processes, including project approval and acceptance based on sound business cases.</p><p>* Support project owners in evaluating proposals by providing relevant insights on value, impact, and strategic alignment.</p><p>* Monitor project KPIs and performance, identifying risks and implementing corrective actions when required.</p><p>* Review and manage project schedules, deliverables, quality, and costs.</p><p>* Prepare and present regular project progress reports to management and stakeholders.</p><p>* Coordinate and maintain project documentation and administrative records.</p><p>* Proactively handle project-related administrative tasks such as meeting coordination, follow-ups, minutes taking, and requirements compilation.</p>",
